content.detailedDescription: I was coming home from the movies heading down rt 44 in lake county going south when i noticed a red blinking light to my right. at first i thought it was just a cell phone tower till we came to a clearing in the trees and it was a little to high for a tower. i watched the red blinking light till we get to the light to turn onto rt 90 going east. when we reached the stop light, the red blinking light then turned into two three lights,. it looked like three small lights, red, wight and blue, but my husband said it wasn���t blue that he thought it was green. the lights just stayed still in the air, that is when i thought it might be a helicopter. my husband then turned on the entente ramp to the highway and i figured i would never see it again. i watched as we drove out of it���s view. i was amazed at what i saw and stared repeatedly looking for it. withing a minuted it came into vew again and was now heading down rt 90 east. as i watched it, it was now just the red light again, then it changed to a bright white light. it was now moving very fast and almost caught up with the car and i thought it was going to fly right over us, then the light flared and became very bright for a second, i watched it the whole way home. my husband was looking at it from the rear view when we saw it flare again. we reached our exit and stopped at the stop sing. i couldn���t believe it, but the light also stopped. as we turned off the ramp onto the road i watched the light, it had stopped and was just sitting there in the sky, i could now see the red light again with the white. i took a drive back up to the highway about 30 min later to see if it was still there and it was gone. i need to know what that was. was it a helicopter or a ufo. please let me know.
content.shape: Unknown
content.summary: Red binking light that changed to white light and flared very birght a few times

content.detailedDescription:
After 11:30pm on sunday 7-22-07 before mid-night we were driving west on ball rd and getting on the 57 freeway to go south then taking the garden grove freeway going west to long beach me and my girlfriend saw a strange whitish light that looked kinda like a sphere.  later we could see different colored lights on it and on (2) occassions could see a small light come out of the craft and move under the craft.  the lights off the craft would appear to go out once and awhile then within seconds laterthe lights would come back on and the sphere would be in a different position in the overcast sky.  

on one occassion the sphere was slowly descending straight down.  the sphere or craft did not move in manner like a commercial jet or a helicopeter.  it looked like it was floating then would disseappear and re-appear shortly later in a different position in the sky and not show how it got to the new position in the sky.

the sphere with lights seem to be fairly large and seem to have also as
much height as it had width and was at least a few miles away and 
may have been over the ocean when we saw it.  at first i thought it might have been part of the moon shining thru the overcast clouds but my friend said definetly not.  then i thought it might be blimp but it moved too strangely with lights of different rows so it was not a blimp either.  we could not believe what we were seeing and it seem to hide itself within the overcast clouds and somtimes we lost visibility for a short while then we would see this object again a few minutes later.

clearly it was not something you would think of as a normal type of
craft.  i am very interested in knowing if anyone else in orange county 
saw this craft on the night of sunday 7-22-07 between 11:30pm and 
midnight also?
content.shape: Sphere
content.summary: Sphere with lights seen in overcast clouds

content.detailedDescription: I always cleaned the dental office where my wife worked at 5:00 p.M. every wednesdays in la mesa ca., about 13 miles from my house.It was about 4:30 p,m, in the summer,we think in 1973. my two daughters, about 9 and 12, were with me.We were traveling down valle vista rd in lakeside, about one half mile from the riverside dr.Intersection, when i saw a movement out of corner of my left eye. i looked to the left and saw a long,large shiney cylinder, domed on both ends.I could see it above and beyond the trees that lined the roadway.It's hard to say but it was maybe fifteen hundred feet high ( it crossed rattlesnake mountain and el cajon city engineers told me it one thousand,one hundred and  ninety-eight feet high) and maybe one thousand to fifteen hundred feet away. with nothing in the air to gage the size and distance, this is a guess, but it was large and close to the ground.It kept pace with my car, no more than thirty-five mph.I parked at riverside dr and shut off the engine. there was no sound from the craft and it was eerie to me.I said,"what's a military helecopter doing out here"? my oldest daughter said,"dad that's no helicopter, it doesn't have a propeller".That's when i got the shock of my life. it had no wings,motors,propellers,vertical nor horizonal stabilizers.I was in awe at this thing.It was traveling north to south from lakeside to el cajon ca.The evening sun was shining on just the middle of the body where there was a narrow shiney band from the front dome to the back dome.We could not see  windows nor anything but a shiney smooth surface from dome to dome.We watched for maybe fifteen to twenty minutes. it finally disappeared beyond rattlesnake mountain. we went on to the dental office and told my wife and the dentist what we had seen my wife belived us but the dentist scoffed at all three of us and said we were crazy or seeing things. no amount of talking would change his mind. i called a friend that worked at the sheriff's office but no one had made a report.If anyone saw it they may have gotten the same flack i did.I saw you on larry king live and decided to make a report.Every word is true.
content.shape: Cylinder
content.summary: Saw large cylinder cross river valley in lakeside south to city el cajon

content.detailedDescription: My mother called me in because it was getting dark. something caught my eye. i looked up and this spacecraft came in so fast it left a trail. it stopped immediately. i watched it for maybe 30 seconds, then it took off so fast it left another trail. it left in an arch. i have never called it a ufo, it was definitely a spacecraft. there were lights on the craft, but i do not remember what color they were.
content.shape: Circle
content.summary: Came down fast. stopped now. flew off in arch

content.detailedDescription:
Simple event, sorry i don't have more details.  we were driving south on northbend rd near i74 interchange.  time was approx 9:30 pm. and saw directly overhead an orange / red sphere with a cone shaped side.

it was travelling slow from east to west and then dropped quickly out of sight.  believe it descended.

two adults, two teens and 3 kids saw it.  kids panicked, i told them it was a hot air baloon.  kids stated it appeared to have a flames on it.  i told them it was a "hot air balloon on fire".

there was nothing on the news as i've checked.  i know others saw it as i saw people pointing and looking up in amazement.
content.shape: Sphere
content.summary: Red sphere over cincinnati

content.detailedDescription: I was walking my dog in the front yard.  i had seen some meteor action as is usual almost any night when i saw a large bright light or silvery object in the sky approximately 15-20 degrees south and 3-5 degrees east as i stood in front of my house.  i first thought the object was a airplane with full landing lights on but then it came down further twards the earth and moved more northward and grew to about two or three times it's original size.  at this ime i was thinking satilite or space junk hit by the sun.  i have seen satilite orbits from south to north from time to time and i know what they are.  the object had grown to about 8-10 times it's original size and i could not see any visible landing lights nor hear any sound.  it was still moving down and twards the north at a 30 degree angle getting larger and brighter and still more silvery. it was larger than any fixed wing air craft i have seen because the stealth bomber flew over during a fly-in event and also a-10 warthogs practiced in our rolling hills for the gulf war years ago so i know the differences in size as to altitude. we also have the eaa fly in close by and i have seen large and crazy designs.  the object then vanished completely as it appeared with no trace or trail or sound or anything.  i'm not convinced that this is an et ufo. this is the same area that, maybe 10-15 mi. north of here yet, that x-files considered a ufo hot spot along with a genuine ufo bar in dundee. i have lived here most of my life and farmed a lot of this country and until now never seen anything i could not explain. i am an unbeliever but i thought you may have an explaination for this or may find this interesting.  i am not prone to histereics nor am i shaken very easily.  this was plain and simple an interesting happening.

content.detailedDescription: This happened in the early afternoon, the weather was dul and cloudy. i was out in a field next to the old shool building walking the dog when i noticed a dark shape out of the corner of my eye just below cloud level. before i could get a proper look the object darted vertically upward into the clouds making no sound whatsover. at first i thought it was a balloon or something but after a short while it descended out of the cloud again. it hung there for about ten seconds before darting upward again. this repeated four or five times and i managed to get a picture on my phone. after the object dissapeard for the last time i waited 10-15 mins for it to return but it never did.

content.detailedDescription: My friend derek and i were driving out in the country because we were bored.  willie was in the back seat but he tells us he could not see anything.  we had been driving for about an hour and were talking to each other.  the streak appeared shortly after we had turned around to head back.  it came from behind the car and moved very quickly.  we were going about 60.  it was pretty high up and far away i think.  it was green.  it disappeared after about two seconds.  i couldn't make out the shape but i could tell it was moving pretty fast.  when i saw it my mouth hung open and i was kinda in awe.  i felt like the moment had slowed down a bit. there was a silence between me and derek for a few seconds.  after that it was all we could talk about till we got home.  willie didn't see anything he says.
content.shape: Flash
content.summary: Green streak that came from behind our car and disappeared overhead.

content.detailedDescription: We started off the evening in search of some adventure and bummed around uptown and downtown for a while til we got bored and just started driving out into the country.  i was driving, with 2 friends in the van with me.  we headed west on excelsior blvd. until it met up with highway 7 and continued west on that past st. bonifacius til we started running a bit low on gas.  it was probably around 3:15 or so when we started to head back.  after driving for a few minutes, we saw a green flash of light streaking downwards out of the front windshield.  my first though was that it was a firework of some type, since there was green light shooting out behind it, but it didn't explode, and whoever launched it would have to have been just about stright above us and up in a balloon or something.  anyways, the object didn't appear to touch down or anything, but disapeared about halfway down to the horizon.  it all happened very quickely, under a second, and i probably would have dissmissed it as a shooting star if it hadn't been a vivid green color.  we slowed down the van a bit hopeing to see more, but we didn't, so we continued on home.  i had goosebumbs for a few minutes, and then we were just really excited.  and that's pretty much the end of the tale!
content.shape: Other
content.summary: Driving back to the twin cities along highway 7, saw a strange green streak of light.
